headline: ONEOK (OKE): Profit Margin Decline Reinforces Market’s Focus on Slower Earnings Growth
summary: ONEOK (OKE) posted a 19.3% rise in earnings over the past year, although this is notably slower than the company’s 5-year average of 25% annual growth. Net profit margins narrowed to 10.6%, down from 14% last year, signaling moderating profitability even as revenue and earnings continue to climb, albeit at a slower pace.
